"<p>IV.</p><p></p><p>My father-in-law is incredibly allergic to fresh peaches,<br/>any stone fruit really,<br/>but peaches were especially common<br/>and were always there to eat.<br/>He would be with people who were eating them,<br/>and he assumed that everyone else felt the same terrible constriction of the throat,<br/>the same anxiety and discomfort.<br/>They all appeared to be smiling,<br/>and biting in he would smile also,<br/>wondering in secret what the all-fired attraction to these toxic bulbs was even about.</p><p></p><p><a href=\"http://www.penny-arcade.com/2011/3/14/\">(source)</a></p>"